ce:section.ce:para:
The real sample application of biosensors has laid a foundation for the point-of-care experiments of diseases (Fan et al., 2016; Yu et al., 2013). To verify the practicability of the proposed method, we used this method to determine the concentration of GSH in human serum and ADA in flour, respectively. In addition, we evaluated the accuracy of this method by calculating the recovery rate of samples by the standard addition method. The recoveries of GSH detection are between 90.90% and 99.88% (
                        Table 3
                        ), which indicated that the ratio fluorescence sensor has satisfactory applicability in human serum samples. Moreover, the recoveries of ADA analysis are between 98.22% and 102.20%.
